In the following description, like parts are designated by like reference numbers throughout the several drawings.


FIGS. 1A and 1B are center section views of a camera using a conventional mirror device;


FIG. 2 illustrates the operation of a conventional mirror holder;


FIGS. 3A and 3B show the construction of a conventional main mirror drive mechanism;


FIGS. 4A and 4B show the construction of a conventional sub-mirror drive mechanism;


FIGS. 5A and 5B show the construction of the mirror drive mechanism of an embodiment of the present invention; and


FIG. 6 illustrates conventional mirror adjustment;


FIG. 7 illustrates the operation of the mirror device according to one embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 8 illustrates an operational center section view of a camera having a mirror device according to one embodiment of the present invention;


FIG. 9 illustrates an operational front view of a mirror device according to one embodiment of the present invention, where the main mirror and the sub-mirror are located in the retracted or exposure position; and


FIG. 10 illustrates an operational front view of a mirror device according to one embodiment of the present invention, where the main mirror and the sub-mirror are located in the unretracted or exposure preparation position.
